#, no-wrap
msgid "Advices and guidelines"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:6
msgid ""
"This page lists some advice and guidelines which every YunoHost "
"administrator should be aware to take care of a YunoHost server :)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do not break YunoHost"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:10
msgid ""
"To put it another way: your server is either a production server (meant to "
"work) or a test server on which you allow yourself to experiment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:12
msgid "If your goal is to run a production server:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:18
msgid ""
"be aware that servers are fragile system. Stay cautious, methodical and "
"patient;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:18
msgid ""
"limit experimentations and customizations (for instance of config file);"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:18
msgid "do not install dozens of apps just to see how they look;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:18
msgid ""
"use non-official apps with caution, and do not use apps that are still 'in "
"progress', 'not working' or level 0;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:18
msgid ""
"if something gets broken, think twice about fixing it by yourself if you "
"don't know what you are doing. <small>(For instance, do not attempt to "
"recreate yourself the admin user just because it mysteriously "
"disappeared...)</small>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Keep it simple!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:22
msgid ""
"YunoHost is designed to work with general and simple use cases in mind. "
"Deviating from those conditions will make things harder and you will need "
"technical knowledge to make it work. For instance:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:28
msgid ""
"do not try to run YunoHost in a context where you cannot have control over "
"ports 80 and 443 (or no internet at all);"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:28
msgid ""
"do not try to host five servers behind the same internet connection if you "
"are not already an advanced user;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:28
msgid ""
"do not fall into nerd whims such as willing to replace NGINX with Apache (or "
"run both at the same time);"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:28
msgid ""
"do not try to use custom SSL certificates if you don't really need them;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:30
msgid "Keep things as simple as you can!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do not reinstall every day"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:34
msgid ""
"Some people tend to fall into \"the reinstallation spiral\" - where each "
"time something breaks in the server and it is not obvious how to fix it, or "
"because the server became \"dirty\", one ends up reinstalling the whole "
"server from scratch because it looks like an \"easy\" and quick solution to "
"clean the table."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:36
msgid ""
"Please don't do this. Reinstalling is a heavy operation and is not a good "
"long-term strategy for fixing problems. You will get tired and won't learn "
"anything. Forget the dream of having a \"clean\" server. A real-life server "
"always end up being a bit \"dirty\". Also, you need to (progressively) learn "
"how to solve issues when you encounter them. Reach for [help](/community/"
"help) with detailed symptoms of what you are trying to do and what is "
"happening, and fix the issues. Over time, you will get a much better control "
"over your server than just blindly reinstalling every time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do backups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:40
msgid ""
"If you host services and data that are important for your users, it is "
"important that you setup a backup policy. Backups can be easily created from "
"the webadmin - you can download it from the webadmin or via your favorite "
"FTP client, such as FileZilla or your own terminal. You should perform "
"backup regularly and keep them in a safe and different physical location "
"from your server. More info on [the backup documentation](/admin/backups)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Check rootâ€™s email"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:44
msgid ""
"As an administrator, you should configure an email client to check emails "
"sent to `root@your.domain.tld` (which should be an alias to the first user "
"your added) or otherwise forward them to another address that you actively "
"check. Those mails may contain information on what is happening on your "
"server such as automated periodic tasks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "YunoHost is free software, maintained by volunteers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:48
msgid ""
"Finally, keep in mind that YunoHost is a free software maintained by "
"volunteers - and that the goal of YunoHost (to democratize self-hosting) is "
"not an easy one! It is provided without any warranty. The team of volunteers "
"does its best to maintain and provide the best possible experience - yet "
"features, applications and YunoHost as a whole are far from being perfect "
"and you will experience small and big shortcomings at some points. When this "
"happens, kindly [reach for help on the chat or forum, or report the issue](/"
"community/help)! :)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:50
msgid ""
"If you like YunoHost and want to see the project being kept alive and make "
"progress, feel free to leave a thank you note and to [donate](https://"
"liberapay.com/YunoHost) to the project and talk about it around you!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/90.guidelines.mdx:51
msgid ""
"Last but not least, since YunoHost is a free software project, you are "
"legitimate and welcomed to come and [contribute](/dev/) to the project, be "
"it on the technical aspects (i.e. code) and less-technical aspects (such as "
"contributing to this documentation! ;))"
msgstr ""
